{"title":"Cyclist Track Days 2025 bikes #4: Orbea Orca","link":"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/cyclist-track-days-2025-bikes-orbea-orca","date":1740761979000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/cyclist-track-days-2025-bikes-orbea-orca\">Cyclist Track Days 2025 bikes #4: Orbea Orca</a></p>\n\n<p>Whether you are in the market for a new bike or just want to try out some of the best bikes in the world, <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/cyclist-track-days-information\">Cyclist Track Days</a> offer a unique experience to test the latest top-end bikes from the leading brands on the market. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The next bike in our run through of the incredible bikes available to test ride at this years Track Days is the Orbea Orca.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Ridden by the Lotto pro team, the Orca is Orbea’s<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/buying-guides/best-lightweight-road-bikes\"> lightweight bike</a>, perfect for climbing.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em>Cyclist</em> writer Joseph Delves reviewed the top spec M10i LTD model in 2024 and said it was ‘far more than a mountain specialist’, citing its surprising speed and ‘ineffable loveliness’, thanks in part due to its classic look and feel.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The bike you’ll be testing at the Cyclist Track Day in London will be the Orbea Orca M20i Team, which is built with a Shimano Ultegra Di2 groupset and Orbea’s Oquo brand wheels, and retails for £5,999.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can read Joseph’s full review <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/reviews/orbea-orca-m10i-ltd-road-bike-review\">here</a>. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The Orbea Orca will be at the following Track Days event:</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>17<sup>th</sup> May 2025, Lee Valley VeloPark London</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>For more information on Cyclist Track Days click <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/cyclist-track-days-information\">here</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://www.eventbrite.com/cc/cyclist-track-days-2025-3855053\" t